  {
    "type": "qa_answer",
    "data": {
      "answer": "Atomic writes here use a temp-file + rename pattern: write to `<path>.tmp.<ts>`, then `rename()` is the commit point. The OS rename is atomic so a crash mid-write leaves the original file intact, and a partial temp-file is harmless. fsync is not called explicitly — durability after rename is best-effort and depends on the host filesystem.",
